- Assignment does not create a copy
a = [1, 2, 3]
b = a

- This does not create two lists. It creates two names pointing to the same list.

- To create a new list, use .copy().

a = [1, 2, 3]
b = a.copy()

b.append(4)

print(a)
print(b)

- copy using slicing:

a = [1, 2, 3]
b = a[:]

b.append(4)

print(a)
print(b)

- Both .copy() and [:] create a shallow copy.